                                                                Python Basic (Operattion & Type Conversion)

 1> Operation = Operation are symbols used to perform operation on values
                 or variables.


   # Arithmetic Operation
  
   + = Addition
   - = Substraction
   * = Multiplication
   / = Division
   % = Modulus (Remainder)
   // = Floor division
   ** = Exponent (Power)
 
 # Assignment Operator
 
 = The assignment operator (=) is used to assign
   a value to a variable.

 
  Example:
  
  name = "Aman"
  age = 18

 Here:
name,age -- Variables
"Aman",18 -- values
= -- Assignment Operator


 # Comparison Operators
 = Comparison operators compare two values and return
   either True or False.

  == Equal to
  != Not equal to
  > Greater than
  < Less than
  >= Greater than or equal to
 <= Less than or equal to

 # Logical Opreator
= Logical operators are used to combine multiple
  conditions.

  and = True only if both conditions are True.
  or = True if at least one condition is True.
  not = Reverse the Boolean value.


2> Type Conversion
  = Type Conversion is the process of converting one
    data tpe into another.

  # Common Type Conversion Functions
 
    int()  Converts data into integer
    float() Converts data into Float.
   str()  Converts data into string.
   bool()  Converts into Boolean.


